Write a Streamlit web app called app.py for a "Wealth Portfolio Advisor" that:

UI:

Title: "📈 Wealth Portfolio Advisor"
Subtitle: "AI-powered portfolio analysis"
Sidebar: text area where user enters portfolio as CSV format: TICKER,SHARES like "RELIANCE.NS,50" one per line. Add a default example with 5 Indian stocks (RELIANCE.NS, TCS.NS, INFY.NS, HDFCBANK.NS, WIPRO.NS)
"Analyse Portfolio" button


When button clicked:

Parse the portfolio input
Use yfinance to fetch: current price, 3-month history, company name, sector for each ticker
Calculate: current value per stock, total portfolio value, % allocation per stock, 3-month return % per stock
Show 3 metrics at top: Total Portfolio Value, Best Performer, Worst Performer
Show plotly pie chart: portfolio allocation by stock
Show plotly line chart: 3-month price performance for all stocks (normalised to 100)
Show a holdings table: ticker, company, shares, current price, current value, 3-month return %


AI Analysis section:

Send portfolio data to Claude (claude-sonnet-4-5, max_tokens=1000)
System prompt: "You are a senior Indian wealth advisor. Analyse this portfolio and give practical advice."
Ask Claude to provide: portfolio health summary, concentration risks, top recommendation, one rebalancing suggestion, market context
Display Claude's analysis in a clean info box


Handle errors gracefully (invalid tickers, network issues)
Use st.session_state to cache results
Add clear comments